This paper is about a query language for property graphs, which are commonly used in databases and data science. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of temporal data types and functions, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of extensions, which suggests a connection to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
